142711.name: cumulative_tests_per_case
142711.description: The total number of tests to date divided by the total number of confirmed cases. Tests may refer to the number of tests performed or the number of people tested – depending on which is reported by the particular country.

source.name: Official data collated by Our World in Data – Last updated 14 December 2021, 17:20 (London time)
source.additionalInfo:
Data on COVID-19 testing. Comparisons between countries are compromised for several reasons.

You can download the full dataset, alongside detailed source descriptions here: https://github.com/owid/covid-19-data/tree/master/public/data/

142717.name: Estimated percentage of symptomatic COVID-19 cases reported
142717.datasetName: Estimated percentage of symptomatic COVID-19 cases reported as of 8 April – Russell et al. (2020)

display.name: Estimated percentage of symptomatic COVID-19 cases reported

source.name: Russell et al. (2020)
source.dataPublishedBy: Russel T., Hellewell J., Abbot S. et al. ‘Using a delay-adjusted case fatality ratio to estimate under-reporting’.
source.additionalInfo:
Estimates from Russel T., Hellewell J., Abbot S. et al. ‘Using a delay-adjusted case fatality ratio to estimate under-reporting’.

The authors estimate the degree to which countries confirmed cases may underestimate total symptomatic cases by applying the case fatality rate observed in large studies in China and South Korea to data on the number of COVID-19 deaths.

The date to which the data relate is not made explicit by the authors, but the figures at the time of retrieval appear to relate to the situation as of 8 April.
